Tony Lip.

265
00:13:20,524 --> 00:13:22,892
No Tony Lip.

266
00:13:22,894 --> 00:13:25,394
No, I should be on there.

267
00:13:25,396 --> 00:13:27,563
Uh...

268
00:13:27,565 --> 00:13:31,600
no, um, I have a Tony Val...
Valle-la-la...

269
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:33,468
Vallelonga. Yeah.

270
00:13:33,470 --> 00:13:35,805
That's me.

271
00:13:35,807 --> 00:13:37,472
Fill it out while you wait.

272
00:13:37,474 --> 00:13:38,674
What?

273
00:13:38,676 --> 00:13:40,742
Fill it out while you wait.

274
00:13:40,744 --> 00:13:42,680
Oh. Yeah.

275
00:14:04,836 --> 00:14:06,503
Have a seat.

276
00:14:34,665 --> 00:14:37,599
Mr. Vallelonga.
Sorry to keep you waiting.

277
00:14:37,601 --> 00:14:38,968
Oh.

278
00:14:40,537 --> 00:14:42,071
I'm Dr. Donald Shirley.

279
00:14:42,073 --> 00:14:43,806
Tony.

280
00:14:43,808 --> 00:14:46,610
Yes. Please sit down.

281
00:14:49,247 --> 00:14:52,015
Some place you got here.

282
00:14:52,017 --> 00:14:54,050
Are them horns real?

283
00:14:54,052 --> 00:14:56,654
Elephant tusks, yes.

284
00:14:57,721 --> 00:14:59,022
What about that?

285
00:14:59,024 --> 00:15:00,658
Is that a molar?

286
00:15:01,993 --> 00:15:03,492
A what?

287
00:15:03,494 --> 00:15:05,794
A molar, a-a shark tooth.

288
00:15:05,796 --> 00:15:08,264
Or a tiger's, maybe.

289
00:15:08,266 --> 00:15:10,833
It was a gift.

290
00:15:10,835 --> 00:15:13,803
I thought, uh... I thought
I was going to an office.

291
00:15:13,805 --> 00:15:16,705
They said a doctor
needed a driver.

292
00:15:16,707 --> 00:15:18,041
That's all they told you?

293
00:15:18,043 --> 00:15:19,775
Yeah.

294
00:15:19,777 --> 00:15:23,712
Actually, it's a bit more
complicated than that.

295
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:25,917
Have you ever driven
professionally before?

296
00:15:26,952 --> 00:15:28,750
Yeah. Sanitation.

297
00:15:28,752 --> 00:15:30,519
Garbage trucks.

298
00:15:30,521 --> 00:15:33,089
Plus, I drive my boss home
at night.

299
00:15:33,091 --> 00:15:34,924
But I can drive anything.

300
00:15:34,926 --> 00:15:36,993
Limos. Tow trucks.

301
00:15:36,995 --> 00:15:38,694
Snowplows. Whatever.

302
00:15:38,696 --> 00:15:39,862
I see.

303
00:15:39,864 --> 00:15:41,797
What other experience
do you have?

304
00:15:41,799 --> 00:15:43,532
I worked a lot of joints.

305
00:15:43,534 --> 00:15:45,802
Wagon Wheel,
Peppermint Lounge, Copa.

306
00:15:45,804 --> 00:15:47,602
In what capacity?

307
00:15:47,604 --> 00:15:48,805
What do you mean?

308
00:15:48,807 --> 00:15:50,739
What did you do there?

309
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:52,476
Uh...

310
00:15:53,577 --> 00:15:55,144
Public relations.

311
00:15:55,146 --> 00:15:58,915
Well, first of all, Tony,
I'm not a medical doctor.

312
00:15:58,917 --> 00:16:00,116
I'm a musician.

313
00:16:00,118 --> 00:16:02,551
You mean, like, songs?

314
00:16:02,553 --> 00:16:03,785
Yes.

315
00:16:03,787 --> 00:16:05,754
And I'm about to embark
on a concert tour,

316
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:07,689
the majority of which
will be down south.

317
00:16:07,691 --> 00:16:08,925
Atlantic City.

318
00:16:08,927 --> 00:16:10,093
No.

319
00:16:10,095 --> 00:16:11,760
The Deep South.

320
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:13,695
First, we're starting
in the Midwest,

321
00:16:13,697 --> 00:16:15,098
and then we're taking
a hard left.

322
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,100
Kentucky, North Carolina,
Tennessee,

323
00:16:17,102 --> 00:16:19,068
and on down through the Delta.

324
00:16:19,070 --> 00:16:22,138
Do you foresee any issues
in working for a black man?

325
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:24,340
No.

326
00:16:24,342 --> 00:16:25,908
No, no, no.

327
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:27,977
It was just the other day,
me and the wife

328
00:16:27,979 --> 00:16:30,015
had a couple of colored guys
over at the house.

329
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:34,050
For-for drinks.

330
00:16:34,052 --> 00:16:35,617
Hmm. I see.

331
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:36,785
You're married.

332
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:39,090
Yeah. Two kids.

333
00:16:40,925 --> 00:16:43,692
I'm not sure this is the
proper job for a married man.

334
00:16:43,694 --> 00:16:45,694
Why? Are we bringing broads?

335
00:16:45,696 --> 00:16:49,165
My point is we'll be gone
for eight straight weeks.

336
00:16:49,167 --> 00:16:51,834
No breaks,
right up until Christmas.

337
00:16:51,836 --> 00:16:54,170
You're quite sure you can leave
your family for that long?

338
00:16:54,172 --> 00:16:56,039
Depends what you're paying.

339
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:58,074
A hundred dollars a week,
plus room and board.

340
00:16:58,076 --> 00:16:59,175
Hmm.

341
00:16:59,177 --> 00:17:01,710
But let me be crystal clear.

342
00:17:01,712 --> 00:17:03,678
I'm not just hiring
a chauffeur.

343
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:06,816
I need someone
who can handle my itinerary.

344
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:09,651
Be a personal assistant.
I need a valet.

345
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:13,124
I need someone who can launder
my clothes and shine my shoes.

346
00:17:15,193 --> 00:17:17,062
Good luck, Doc.

347
00:17:19,763 --> 00:17:21,066
Tony.

348
00:17:26,004 --> 00:17:27,970
I had my record label
ask around town

349
00:17:27,972 --> 00:17:29,906
to find me the right man.

350
00:17:29,908 --> 00:17:32,576
Your name came up
more than once.

351
00:17:33,845 --> 00:17:36,846
You've impressed several people
with your...

352
00:17:36,848 --> 00:17:38,917
innate ability
to handle trouble.

353
00:17:40,118 --> 00:17:42,051
And that is why I called
and inquired

354
00:17:42,053 --> 00:17:44,022
about your availability.

355
00:17:47,058 --> 00:17:48,690
Okay, here's the deal.

356
00:17:48,692 --> 00:17:50,725
I got no problem
being on the road with you.

357
00:17:50,727 --> 00:17:51,861
But I ain't no butler.

358
00:17:51,863 --> 00:17:53,762
I ain't ironing no shirts,

359
00:17:53,764 --> 00:17:55,131
and I'm not polishing
nobody's shoes.

360
00:17:55,133 --> 00:17:57,433
You need somebody to get you
from point A to point B?

361
00:17:57,435 --> 00:17:58,835
You need someone to make sure

362
00:17:58,837 --> 00:18:00,002
there's no problems
along the way?

363
00:18:00,004 --> 00:18:02,004
And believe me,
you and the Deep South,

364
00:18:02,006 --> 00:18:03,840
there's gonna be problems.

365
00:18:03,842 --> 00:18:05,108
So, if you want me,

366
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:07,143
it's a buck and a quarter
a week.

367
00:18:07,145 --> 00:18:09,744
Or go hire that little Chink
just pranced out of here.

368
00:18:09,746 --> 00:18:11,782
See how far you get.

369
00:18:13,218 --> 00:18:16,751
Well, Mr. Vallelonga,

370
00:18:16,753 --> 00:18:19,088
thank you for stopping by.

371
00:18:31,269 --> 00:18:33,269
Hey, Bobby.

372
00:18:33,271 --> 00:18:35,171
Give me a Rheingold.

373
00:18:35,173 --> 00:18:37,041
Ice cold.

374
00:18:46,017 --> 00:18:47,051
Mr. Tony.

375
00:18:48,752 --> 00:18:50,719
Augie asking about you.

376
00:18:52,157 --> 00:18:53,890
Come on!
I'm dying of thirst over here.

377
00:18:53,892 --> 00:18:54,924
Shut up!

378
00:18:54,926 --> 00:18:56,760
I'm talking.

379
00:18:59,497 --> 00:19:00,863
When?

380
00:19:00,865 --> 00:19:03,067
Now. He in his box.

381
00:19:29,194 --> 00:19:30,694
Tony Lip.

382
00:19:32,330 --> 00:19:34,230
What the hell happened
at the Copa?

383
00:19:34,232 --> 00:19:36,167
I hear you almost split
a guy's face open.

384
00:19:37,335 --> 00:19:40,069
That guy you hit,
Mikey Cerrone,

385
00:19:40,071 --> 00:19:42,073
part of
Charlie the Hand's crew.

386
00:19:43,241 --> 00:19:45,243
Guess he should have
known better.

387
00:19:49,547 --> 00:19:51,847
Hand asked me to look into it.

388
00:19:51,849 --> 00:19:53,849
I spoke to Podell.

389
00:19:53,851 --> 00:19:57,055
Whole thing was, uh,
over a piece of ass, right?

390
00:19:58,189 --> 00:20:00,022
Yeah.

391
00:20:00,024 --> 00:20:03,792
Beef like that should never
happen inside the club.

392
00:20:03,794 --> 00:20:05,995
They were out of line.

393
00:20:05,997 --> 00:20:07,999
So we squashed it.

394
00:20:10,001 --> 00:20:12,969
You, uh, looking to earn
a little extra <i>scharole?</i>

395
00:20:12,971 --> 00:20:15,871
I can keep you busy
while the Copa is down.

396
00:20:15,873 --> 00:20:17,175
What do I gotta do?

397
00:20:19,143 --> 00:20:21,179
Things.

398
00:20:23,848 --> 00:20:25,414
Appreciate it, but, uh,

399
00:20:25,416 --> 00:20:27,917
I want to spend some time
with the family.

400
00:20:27,919 --> 00:20:29,819
Don't be stupid.

401
00:20:29,821 --> 00:20:32,922
You make yourself a few extra
bucks, you buy something nice

402
00:20:32,924 --> 00:20:35,191
for that pretty little wife
of yours.

403
00:20:35,193 --> 00:20:37,161
Hmm.

404
00:20:39,264 --> 00:20:41,197
Nah, I'm good.

405
00:20:41,199 --> 00:20:43,167
I'm flush right now.

406
00:20:44,235 --> 00:20:49,005
♪ So long, Lover's Island

407
00:20:49,007 --> 00:20:51,274
- ♪ Dee
- ♪ Dee-ooh

408
00:20:51,276 --> 00:20:53,876
♪ Ee, ah, ooh, ay...

409
00:20:56,347 --> 00:20:58,180
Here's 50.

410
00:20:58,182 --> 00:21:01,152
Here. Pay me 60 by New Year's,
you get it back.

411
00:21:04,122 --> 00:21:06,355
Hey, Lip.

412
00:21:06,357 --> 00:21:08,324
Everything okay?

413
00:21:08,326 --> 00:21:11,062
What, you got
beak trouble, Charlie?

414
00:21:12,196 --> 00:21:14,897
Mind your business.

415
00:21:14,899 --> 00:21:16,198
♪ Lover's Island...

416
00:21:17,635 --> 00:21:19,335
So, come on.
I'm dying to hear.

417
00:21:19,337 --> 00:21:21,070
What happened
with the doctor interview?

418
00:21:21,072 --> 00:21:23,072
He ain't a real doctor.

419
00:21:23,074 --> 00:21:24,473
He's a piano player.

420
00:21:24,475 --> 00:21:26,342
Well, I don't understand.

421
00:21:26,344 --> 00:21:28,210
Why did they say
that he was a doctor?

422
00:21:28,212 --> 00:21:30,346
I don't know.
I think he's, like,

423
00:21:30,348 --> 00:21:32,882
a doctor of, uh,
piano playing or something.

424
00:21:32,884 --> 00:21:34,216
You can be that?

425
00:21:34,218 --> 00:21:35,885
I guess.

426
00:21:35,887 --> 00:21:38,154
He lives on top
of Carnegie Hall.

427
00:21:38,156 --> 00:21:40,022
You should've seen
this place, Dee.

428
00:21:40,024 --> 00:21:42,425
It was filled with statues
and all kinds of fancy crap.

429
00:21:42,427 --> 00:21:44,960
And he was sitting on top
of a friggin' throne

430
00:21:44,962 --> 00:21:47,396
all dressed up like, uh, like
the king of the jungle bunnies.

431
00:21:47,398 --> 00:21:50,268
He's colored?

432
00:21:53,071 --> 00:21:55,104
Well, you wouldn't last
a week with him.

433
00:21:55,106 --> 00:21:57,673
For the right money, I would.

434
00:22:07,251 --> 00:22:09,685
Yeah.

435
00:22:09,687 --> 00:22:11,287
Oh.

436
00:22:11,289 --> 00:22:14,090
Look...

437
00:22:14,092 --> 00:22:15,958
Really?

438
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:17,159
- Uh, okay.
- You okay?

439
00:22:17,161 --> 00:22:18,461
Okay, hang on a sec.

440
00:22:18,463 --> 00:22:22,698
It's, uh, Dr. Shirley,
the piano guy.

441
00:22:22,700 --> 00:22:24,500
He wants to talk to you.

442
00:22:24,502 --> 00:22:26,168
- Me?
- Yeah.

443
00:22:26,170 --> 00:22:27,970
What? No.

444
00:22:27,972 --> 00:22:29,271
Come on.

445
00:22:29,273 --> 00:22:30,506
- Take it.
- No. Tony...

446
00:22:30,508 --> 00:22:32,143
Just... just talk.

447
00:22:35,279 --> 00:22:37,014
Hello?

448
00:22:38,282 --> 00:22:40,383
Uh, good morning, Doctor.

449
00:22:40,385 --> 00:22:42,420
It's nice to talk to you.

450
00:22:47,291 --> 00:22:50,128
Well, uh, yes,
that is a long time.

451
00:22:53,064 --> 00:22:54,365
It is.

452
00:22:56,167 --> 00:22:58,267
Yes. I'm sure.

453
00:22:58,269 --> 00:23:00,202
Thank you.

454
00:23:00,204 --> 00:23:02,405
Thank you for calling.

455
00:23:02,407 --> 00:23:04,041
Bye, now.

456
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:08,279
What'd he say?

457
00:23:09,514 --> 00:23:11,547
He wanted to know
if I'd be okay

458
00:23:11,549 --> 00:23:16,419
with him taking my husband away
from his family for two months.

459
00:23:16,421 --> 00:23:19,924
He said he'd pay you
what you asked for.

460
00:23:24,996 --> 00:23:26,531
- Hey.
- Hmm?

461
00:23:28,332 --> 00:23:30,366
It's good money.

462
00:23:30,368 --> 00:23:32,236
We need it.

463
00:23:34,372 --> 00:23:38,242
Can't be eating 26 hot dogs
every day.

464
00:23:40,077 --> 00:23:42,578
I know.

465
00:23:42,580 --> 00:23:45,918
I told him it was okay
for you to go.

466
00:23:48,119 --> 00:23:50,419
All right, hey, look, so here's
the first half of your pay.

467
00:23:50,421 --> 00:23:52,354
You're gonna get the rest
when the tour's over.

468
00:23:52,356 --> 00:23:54,089
No, I gotta get paid
every week.

469
00:23:54,091 --> 00:23:56,091
Sorry. That's not how
the record company does it.

470
00:23:56,093 --> 00:23:58,260
We got to have some guarantee
you're gonna finish the job.

471
00:23:58,262 --> 00:24:01,163
Why wouldn't I finish the job?
I took it, didn't I?

472
00:24:01,165 --> 00:24:04,500
Well, then we got nothing
to worry about.

473
00:24:04,502 --> 00:24:07,169
Here's the deal,
Mr. Vallelonga.

474
00:24:07,171 --> 00:24:09,538
Okay, it's your job to get Don
to all his tour dates on time.

475
00:24:09,540 --> 00:24:11,073
Now, if he misses any shows,

476
00:24:11,075 --> 00:24:12,274
you're not getting
your back end.

477
00:24:12,276 --> 00:24:14,477
- He's not gonna miss any show.
- Good.

478
00:24:14,479 --> 00:24:17,246
Oh, you're gonna need this.

479
00:24:17,248 --> 00:24:19,315
Now, this is the book
I was telling you about.

480
00:24:19,317 --> 00:24:21,383
Now, sometimes you guys
are staying in the same hotel,

481
00:24:21,385 --> 00:24:23,519
sometimes you're not.

482
00:24:23,521 --> 00:24:26,121
- Oh, yeah, the...
- Yeah, yeah.

483
00:24:26,123 --> 00:24:29,291
All right, don't let me down.
Let's go.

484
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:38,300
<i>Madonne,</i> is this the new one?

485
00:24:38,302 --> 00:24:40,302
Yeah, the record company
rented it.

486
00:24:40,304 --> 00:24:42,071
- It's nice, huh?
- Beautiful.

487
00:24:42,073 --> 00:24:43,672
So, what'd my sister
have to say

488
00:24:43,674 --> 00:24:45,674
about you being gone
for three weeks?

489
00:24:45,676 --> 00:24:48,077
Eight weeks.

490
00:24:48,079 --> 00:24:49,846
Ten to one,
you slap this moolie out,

491
00:24:49,848 --> 00:24:53,148
you come home in under a month.

492
00:24:53,150 --> 00:24:54,851
- Come here.
- All right, boys, huddle up.

493
00:24:54,853 --> 00:24:57,152
- Say good-bye to your father.
- Frankie, Nicky. Come here.

494
00:24:57,154 --> 00:24:58,287
All right.

495
00:24:58,289 --> 00:25:00,155
- You gonna be good boys?
- Uh-huh.

496
00:25:00,157 --> 00:25:01,590
- You'll listen to your mother?
- Mm-hmm.

497
00:25:01,592 --> 00:25:03,459
Yeah? All right, give me a kiss.

498
00:25:03,461 --> 00:25:06,395
I'm counting on youse.

499
00:25:06,397 --> 00:25:09,033
- Don't go too far.
- We won't.

500
00:25:11,435 --> 00:25:14,503
- Did you go to the AAA for the maps?
- Yes.

501
00:25:14,505 --> 00:25:17,172
No. I mean, the record
companies gave me the maps

502
00:25:17,174 --> 00:25:19,176
and the itinerary,
and this thing.

503
00:25:20,444 --> 00:25:22,545
<i>The Negro Motorist's
Green Book.</i>

504
00:25:22,547 --> 00:25:25,548
Yeah, it lists all the places
coloreds can stay down south.

505
00:25:25,550 --> 00:25:28,450
Like a... you know,
traveling while black.

506
00:25:28,452 --> 00:25:31,320
- "Traveling while black"?
- Yeah, if you're black

507
00:25:31,322 --> 00:25:33,188
and you gotta travel,
for some reason.

508
00:25:33,190 --> 00:25:36,191
- Got a special book for that?
- I guess.

509
00:25:36,193 --> 00:25:38,394
- Did you pack the iron?
- I ain't lugging no iron, Dee.

510
00:25:38,396 --> 00:25:40,529
- Come on.
- How are you gonna press your pants, Tony?

511
00:25:40,531 --> 00:25:43,198
I'll put 'em
under the mattress.

512
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:45,267
I want you
to write me a letter.

513
00:25:45,269 --> 00:25:47,336
- Every chance you get.
- I can't write letters.

514
00:25:47,338 --> 00:25:48,905
Yes, you can.

515
00:25:48,907 --> 00:25:50,472
- I can't write.
- Take you five minutes.

516
00:25:50,474 --> 00:25:51,607
- Promise me.
- It's embarrassing.

517
00:25:51,609 --> 00:25:53,409
It ain't gonna be no good.

518
00:25:53,411 --> 00:25:56,178
It's a lot cheaper than
calling long-distance, Tony.

519
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:58,180
Promise me you're gonna write.

520
00:25:58,182 --> 00:26:00,052
I promise.

521
00:26:01,752 --> 00:26:03,752
Dee, put this in a bank today.

522
00:26:03,754 --> 00:26:05,688
It's half my pay.

523
00:26:05,690 --> 00:26:07,723
Oh. Here.
There's a couple of sandwiches

524
00:26:07,725 --> 00:26:09,625
for you and Dr. Shirley.

525
00:26:09,627 --> 00:26:10,693
Thanks.

526
00:26:10,695 --> 00:26:12,227
