919
00:50:03,194 --> 00:50:05,662
Let's hear it.

920
00:50:06,697 --> 00:50:08,797
I have a brother somewhere.

921
00:50:08,799 --> 00:50:11,767
We used to get together
once in a while,

922
00:50:11,769 --> 00:50:14,037
but it got more and more
difficult to stay in touch.

923
00:50:14,039 --> 00:50:17,373
Curse of being
a musician, I guess.

924
00:50:17,375 --> 00:50:19,809
Always on the road.

925
00:50:19,811 --> 00:50:21,911
Like a carnival worker.

926
00:50:21,913 --> 00:50:24,947
- Hmm.
- Or a criminal.

927
00:50:24,949 --> 00:50:27,616
Took quite the toll
on my marriage as well.

928
00:50:27,618 --> 00:50:29,218
- You're married?
- Was.

929
00:50:29,220 --> 00:50:31,154
June.

930
00:50:31,156 --> 00:50:32,989
Good person.

931
00:50:32,991 --> 00:50:35,191
Terrible grammar,
but a kind soul.

932
00:50:35,193 --> 00:50:37,093
You'd quite like her.

933
00:50:37,095 --> 00:50:38,693
June.

934
