01:11:14,332 --> 01:11:16,834
Well, size-wise. Yeah.

1296
01:11:19,070 --> 01:11:21,170
It is about a 42.

1297
01:11:21,172 --> 01:11:24,240
- Why don't you try it on?
- Hmm...

1298
01:11:24,242 --> 01:11:27,276
What, you gotta wear
a tuxedo onstage every night?

1299
01:11:27,278 --> 01:11:29,245
You could mix it up
a little, Doc.

1300
01:11:29,247 --> 01:11:31,113
Come on, let's see
how it looks on you.

1301
01:11:31,115 --> 01:11:32,248
We got plenty of time.

1302
01:11:35,053 --> 01:11:36,652
I'll be right back.

1303
01:11:36,654 --> 01:11:39,488
- How you doing?
- May I help you, sir?

1304
01:11:39,490 --> 01:11:41,357
Yeah, we want
to try on that, uh,

1305
01:11:41,359 --> 01:11:43,059
beautiful gray suit
in the window.

1306
01:11:43,061 --> 01:11:44,327
You got it in a 42?

1307
01:11:44,329 --> 01:11:46,230
Of course.

1308
01:11:48,399 --> 01:11:50,099
That's the one.

1309
01:11:50,101 --> 01:11:51,967
Dressing room
is in the back, sir.

1310
01:11:51,969 --> 01:11:53,336
Thank you.

1311
01:11:53,338 --> 01:11:55,671
- I'll be just a moment.
- Take your time, Doc.

1312
01:11:55,673 --> 01:11:57,408
I'll check out
some ties for you.

1313
01:11:58,976 --> 01:12:00,976
Uh, e-excuse me.

1314
01:12:00,978 --> 01:12:03,348
Uh, you're not allowed
to try that on.

1315
01:12:04,982 --> 01:12:06,315
I beg your pardon?

1316
01:12:06,317 --> 01:12:08,684
Uh, if you'd like
to purchase it first,

1317
01:12:08,686 --> 01:12:11,389
we'd be happy
to tailor it to your needs.

1318
01:12:13,491 --> 01:12:16,227
I see.

1319
01:13:17,321 --> 01:13:19,023
Yeah.

1320
01:13:20,158 --> 01:13:21,993
That's me.

1321
01:13:32,570 --> 01:13:34,336
Hey, Officer.

1322
01:13:34,338 --> 01:13:36,439
I got a call about Dr. Shirley.

1323
01:13:36,441 --> 01:13:38,476
Come on.

1324
01:13:43,147 --> 01:13:45,481
His friend's here.

1325
01:13:45,483 --> 01:13:47,483
Thank you.

1326
01:13:52,089 --> 01:13:54,523
Get a guy a towel,
for Christ's sake.

1327
01:13:54,525 --> 01:13:56,225
You a lawyer?

1328
01:13:56,227 --> 01:13:57,493
- No.
- Well, you should call one.

1329
01:13:57,495 --> 01:13:59,428
- We're taking your auntie in.
- For what?

1330
01:13:59,430 --> 01:14:02,233
Manager caught him
and the other guy.

1331
01:14:05,603 --> 01:14:08,204
Well, can we get
the cuffs off him,

1332
01:14:08,206 --> 01:14:10,439
let him put his pants on,
we talk about this?

1333
01:14:10,441 --> 01:14:12,107
Sure, we could.

1334
01:14:12,109 --> 01:14:14,076
But we ain't.

1335
01:14:14,078 --> 01:14:17,112
Okay, look, we're out of here
tomorrow morning.

1336
01:14:17,114 --> 01:14:18,547
You'll never see us again.

1337
01:14:18,549 --> 01:14:21,118
There's gotta be something
we can do to work this out.

1338
01:14:23,087 --> 01:14:24,253
What if you let him go

1339
01:14:24,255 --> 01:14:26,388
and I give you something
to thank you?

1340
01:14:27,625 --> 01:14:29,625
- You bribing us?
- No.

1341
01:14:29,627 --> 01:14:31,060
Hell no.

1342
01:14:31,062 --> 01:14:32,228
A gift.

1343
01:14:32,230 --> 01:14:33,529
A thank-you.

1344
01:14:33,531 --> 01:14:36,065
What kind of thank-you?

1345
01:14:36,067 --> 01:14:37,600
Like a...

1346
01:14:37,602 --> 01:14:39,568
you know, donation
to the police force.

1347
01:14:39,570 --> 01:14:41,270
Youse guys.

1348
01:14:41,272 --> 01:14:43,339
Whatever you want.

1349
01:14:43,341 --> 01:14:46,108
You like suits?

1350
01:14:46,110 --> 01:14:48,210
I was walking through
your nice town today,

1351
01:14:48,212 --> 01:14:51,247
and I seen a store
that was selling suits.

1352
01:14:51,249 --> 01:14:53,115
Primo suits.

1353
01:14:53,117 --> 01:14:56,585
What if, as a thank-you...
a donation...

1354
01:14:56,587 --> 01:14:59,555
I buy youse each a suit?

1355
01:14:59,557 --> 01:15:01,357
You get all dressed up,

1356
01:15:01,359 --> 01:15:03,559
you take the wife out
for dinner.

1357
01:15:03,561 --> 01:15:05,561
I mean, guys like you,
you work hard.

1358
01:15:05,563 --> 01:15:07,565
You deserve it.

1359
01:15:14,238 --> 01:15:16,238
They were wrong
for the way they treated me,

1360
01:15:16,240 --> 01:15:18,309
and you rewarded them.

1361
01:15:20,111 --> 01:15:22,444
I was hired to get you
from one show to the next.

1362
01:15:22,446 --> 01:15:24,280
How I do it
shouldn't matter to you.

1363
01:15:24,282 --> 01:15:26,148
I just wish you hadn't
paid 'em off.

1364
01:15:26,150 --> 01:15:28,484
I did what I had to do.

1365
01:15:28,486 --> 01:15:30,887
You know, if this got out,
it would kill your career.

1366
01:15:30,889 --> 01:15:33,188
Okay, Tony.

1367
01:15:33,190 --> 01:15:35,224
I need you to stop it
with the phony altruism

1368
01:15:35,226 --> 01:15:36,659
and concern for my career.

1369
01:15:36,661 --> 01:15:38,394
What the hell does that mean?

1370
01:15:38,396 --> 01:15:40,195
You were only thinking
about yourself back there

1371
01:15:40,197 --> 01:15:41,597
because you know,
if I miss a show,

1372
01:15:41,599 --> 01:15:43,198
it'll come out
of your pocketbook.

1373
01:15:43,200 --> 01:15:45,234
Of course I don't want you
to miss a show,

1374
01:15:45,236 --> 01:15:46,435
you ungrateful bastard.

1375
01:15:46,437 --> 01:15:48,537
You think I'm doing this
for my health?

1376
01:15:48,539 --> 01:15:50,606
Tonight, I saved your ass.

1377
01:15:50,608 --> 01:15:53,309
So show a little
appreciation, maybe.

1378
01:15:53,311 --> 01:15:57,613
Besides, I told you never
to go nowhere without me!

1379
01:15:57,615 --> 01:16:01,650
I assumed you'd want this
to be the exception.

1380
01:16:36,220 --> 01:16:38,520
Want me to get some makeup
or something

1381
01:16:38,522 --> 01:16:39,755
for the show tomorrow?

1382
01:16:39,757 --> 01:16:41,357
No, I'm fine.

1383
01:16:41,359 --> 01:16:43,525
You sure? Bruise kind of shows.

1384
01:16:43,527 --> 01:16:44,729
I said I'm fine.

1385
01:16:46,263 --> 01:16:48,232
Okay.

1386
01:16:54,672 --> 01:16:56,505
He didn't ask me to do that.

1387
01:16:56,507 --> 01:16:58,674
Dom, I'm telling you,
that's what he told me.

1388
01:16:58,676 --> 01:17:00,275
He didn't ask me.

1389
01:17:00,277 --> 01:17:02,778
Oh. Tony Lip.

1390
01:17:02,780 --> 01:17:04,380
- Dominic, Mags.
- What the hell...?

1391
01:17:04,382 --> 01:17:05,748
What the hell you guys
doing down here?

1392
01:17:05,750 --> 01:17:07,282
Hey, Brooklyn sent us down.

1393
01:17:07,284 --> 01:17:09,487
- Take care of a few things.
- Yeah.

1394
01:17:44,321 --> 01:17:46,158
I'm working here.

1395
01:17:55,033 --> 01:17:57,599
Sorry, Doc. They're some
friends from New York.

1396
01:17:57,601 --> 01:17:59,601
Hey, can you get
Dr. Shirley's luggage?

1397
01:17:59,603 --> 01:18:00,705
All right.

1398
01:18:33,537 --> 01:18:34,871
Called his room.

1399
01:18:34,873 --> 01:18:36,707
Be down in a minute.

1400
01:18:45,449 --> 01:18:46,816
Hey, Doc.

1401
01:18:46,818 --> 01:18:48,686
Where are you off to?

1402
01:18:50,321 --> 01:18:52,354
Just going downstairs.

1403
01:18:52,356 --> 01:18:54,291
To have a drink.

1404
01:19:04,602 --> 01:19:06,401
Tony...

1405
01:19:06,403 --> 01:19:10,106
I think you're doing
a wonderful job.

1406
01:19:10,108 --> 01:19:12,374
So...

1407
01:19:12,376 --> 01:19:13,877
I'd like to formally offer you

1408
01:19:13,879 --> 01:19:15,677
the position
of my road manager.

1409
01:19:15,679 --> 01:19:20,582
With the title also comes
more responsibility, but...

1410
01:19:20,584 --> 01:19:22,586
that also means a raise in pay.

1411
01:19:23,654 --> 01:19:25,754
No. No.

1412
01:19:25,756 --> 01:19:28,724
No, thanks.

1413
01:19:28,726 --> 01:19:32,896
We agreed on 125 a week,
plus expenses.

1414
01:19:32,898 --> 01:19:35,834
That's our deal, right?

1415
01:19:37,501 --> 01:19:39,434
I ain't going nowhere, Doc.

1416
01:19:39,436 --> 01:19:41,739
I-I was just going down
to tell them.

1417
01:19:52,416 --> 01:19:53,584
Tony.

1418
01:19:58,455 --> 01:20:00,826
I'm sorry about last night.

1419
01:20:03,962 --> 01:20:06,397
Don't worry about it.

1420
01:20:07,933 --> 01:20:11,400
I've been working nightclubs
in New York City my whole life.

1421
01:20:11,402 --> 01:20:15,472
I know it's a...
complicated world.

1422
01:20:27,718 --> 01:20:29,451
<i>So, where'd you learn</i>

1423
01:20:29,453 --> 01:20:30,686
how to play like that?

1424
01:20:30,688 --> 01:20:32,621
- My mother.
- Your mother?

1425
01:20:32,623 --> 01:20:34,592
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

1426
01:20:36,460 --> 01:20:39,896
She taught me how to play
on an old spinet.

1427
01:20:39,898 --> 01:20:42,464
Soon as I could walk, we'd...

1428
01:20:42,466 --> 01:20:44,700
travel around
the Florida Panhandle,

1429
01:20:44,702 --> 01:20:48,437
put on my little shows
in parishes and halls.

1430
01:20:48,439 --> 01:20:50,639
Fortunately,
a man who had seen me play

1431
01:20:50,641 --> 01:20:51,908
arranged for me to study

1432
01:20:51,910 --> 01:20:53,943
at the Leningrad Conservatory
of Music.

1433
01:20:53,945 --> 01:20:56,778
I was the first Negro
ever accepted there.

1434
01:20:56,780 --> 01:20:59,215
That's where they taught you
all them songs you play?

1435
01:20:59,217 --> 01:21:02,451
Actually, I was trained
to play classical music.

1436
01:21:02,453 --> 01:21:06,724
Brahms, Franz Liszt,
Beethoven, Chopin.

1437
01:21:07,791 --> 01:21:10,059
It's all I ever wanted to play.

1438
01:21:10,061 --> 01:21:12,996
But I was persuaded
by my record company

1439
01:21:12,998 --> 01:21:16,866
to pursue a career
in popular music instead.

1440
01:21:16,868 --> 01:21:19,468
They insisted that audiences
would never accept

1441
01:21:19,470 --> 01:21:21,637
a Negro pianist
on a classical stage.

1442
01:21:21,639 --> 01:21:26,541
Wanted to turn me into just
another colored entertainer.

1443
01:21:26,543 --> 01:21:29,946
You know, the guy who's smoking
while he's playing

1444
01:21:29,948 --> 01:21:32,815
and sets a glass of whiskey
on his piano,

1445
01:21:32,817 --> 01:21:35,550
and then complains
because he's not respected

1446
01:21:35,552 --> 01:21:36,953
like Arthur Rubinstein.

1447
01:21:36,955 --> 01:21:39,856
You don't see Arthur Rubinstein

1448
01:21:39,858 --> 01:21:42,493
putting a glass of whiskey
on his piano.

1449
01:21:43,828 --> 01:21:45,862
I don't know.
Personally, I think,

1450
01:21:45,864 --> 01:21:47,663
if you stuck
to the classic stuff,

1451
01:21:47,665 --> 01:21:49,265
it would've been a big mistake.

1452
01:21:49,267 --> 01:21:50,867
A mistake?

1453
01:21:50,869 --> 01:21:54,103
Performing the music I trained
my entire life to play?

1454
01:21:54,105 --> 01:21:56,705
Trained?
What are you, a seal?

1455
01:21:56,707 --> 01:21:58,573
People love what you do.

1456
01:21:58,575 --> 01:22:01,010
Anyone could sound
like Beethoven or...

1457
01:22:01,012 --> 01:22:03,578
"Joe Pan"
or them other guys you said,

1458
01:22:03,580 --> 01:22:07,518
but your music, what you do...

1459
01:22:08,954 --> 01:22:10,754
...only you can do that.

1460
01:22:13,624 --> 01:22:14,993
Thank you, Tony.

1461
01:22:19,998 --> 01:22:22,633
But not everyone
can play Chopin.

1462
01:22:23,734 --> 01:22:25,736
Not like I can.

1463
01:22:27,005 --> 01:22:29,538
♪ I love my baby...

1464
01:22:29,540 --> 01:22:32,141
<i>"The trees have shed
their leafy clothing,</i>

1465
01:22:32,143 --> 01:22:35,744
and their colors have faded
to grays and browns."

1466
01:22:35,746 --> 01:22:39,614
"I saw millions of trees
all dusted with snow,

1467
01:22:39,616 --> 01:22:41,550
just like out of a fairy tale."

1468
01:22:41,552 --> 01:22:43,853
He's so expressive.

1469
01:22:43,855 --> 01:22:46,122
- "It's getting cold."
- Got to admit, Lip's letters,

1470
01:22:46,124 --> 01:22:47,991
they're not bad.

1471
01:22:47,993 --> 01:22:49,758
Oh, well, it's in the family.

1472
01:22:49,760 --> 01:22:52,028
They say our
great-great-great-grandfather

1473
01:22:52,030 --> 01:22:54,596
helped da Vinci
with the Sixteen Chapel.

1474
01:22:54,598 --> 01:22:56,933
- You mean Michelangelo.
- Right.

1475
01:22:56,935 --> 01:22:59,135
What does Michelangelo have
to do with writing letters?

1476
01:22:59,137 --> 01:23:01,904
I'm just saying,
we're an arty family.

1477
01:23:01,906 --> 01:23:06,142
"I will count the hours,
minutes and seconds

1478
01:23:06,144 --> 01:23:08,643
"until you are in my arms.

1479
01:23:08,645 --> 01:23:10,612
"Love you, Tony.

1480
01:23:10,614 --> 01:23:11,916
P.S. Kiss the kids."

1481
01:23:12,951 --> 01:23:14,150
John!

1482
01:23:14,152 --> 01:23:15,650
Yeah?

1483
01:23:15,652 --> 01:23:17,820
I want a letter.

1484
01:23:17,822 --> 01:23:19,155
Yeah, soon as you make a meal.

1485
01:23:33,604 --> 01:23:37,373
Eyes forward, Tony.

1486
01:24:01,665 --> 01:24:02,932
Tony.

1487
01:24:02,934 --> 01:24:04,233
<i>All right, everybody.</i>

1488
01:24:04,235 --> 01:24:07,103
Let's give our finest
Louisiana welcome

1489
01:24:07,105 --> 01:24:10,039
to Don Shirley
and the Don Shirley Trio.

1490
01:24:36,801 --> 01:24:39,035
Your mother's ass.

1491
01:24:39,037 --> 01:24:41,204
Can't see shit.

1492
01:24:48,679 --> 01:24:50,679
What the hell's this guy doing?

1493
01:24:54,119 --> 01:24:56,221
Son of a bitch.

1494
01:25:08,699 --> 01:25:10,299
License and papers.

1495
01:25:10,301 --> 01:25:13,236
Am I glad to see you.

1496
01:25:13,238 --> 01:25:15,071
We had to turn
off the main road,

1497
01:25:15,073 --> 01:25:18,042
and, uh, now we're lost.

1498
01:25:19,743 --> 01:25:21,743
Step out of the car.

1499
01:25:21,745 --> 01:25:23,079
What'd I do?

1500
01:25:23,081 --> 01:25:24,916
Out of the car.

1501
01:25:36,060 --> 01:25:38,127
Why are you on this road?

1502
01:25:38,129 --> 01:25:39,495
I told you.

1503
01:25:39,497 --> 01:25:43,067
We had to make a detour,
and we got lost.

1504
01:25:47,505 --> 01:25:49,338
And why are you driving him?

1505
01:25:49,340 --> 01:25:51,943
He's my boss.

1506
01:25:57,748 --> 01:25:59,815
He can't be out here at night.

1507
01:25:59,817 --> 01:26:01,750
This is a sundown town.

1508
01:26:01,752 --> 01:26:03,054
What's that?

1509
01:26:04,355 --> 01:26:07,156
Get him out of the car
and check his I.D.

1510
01:26:07,158 --> 01:26:08,324
Oh, come on.

1511
01:26:08,326 --> 01:26:09,458
It's pouring rain.

1512
01:26:09,460 --> 01:26:12,794
Sir, I can just get it
right here through the window.

1513
01:26:12,796 --> 01:26:13,996
Get him out of the car.

1514
01:26:13,998 --> 01:26:15,865
Come on, get out, now.

1515
01:26:15,867 --> 01:26:17,766
Get out, now. Get out.

1516
01:26:17,768 --> 01:26:20,171
Got I.D.?

1517
01:26:22,207 --> 01:26:25,174
How you say this last name?

1518
01:26:25,176 --> 01:26:27,310
Vallelonga.

1519
01:26:27,312 --> 01:26:29,778
Yeah, what kind of name
is that?

1520
01:26:29,780 --> 01:26:31,147
It's Italian.

1521
01:26:31,149 --> 01:26:32,281
Oh.

1522
01:26:32,283 --> 01:26:33,883
Oh, I see.

1523
01:26:33,885 --> 01:26:36,187
That's why
you're driving him around.

1524
01:26:38,223 --> 01:26:39,989
You're half a nigger yourself.

1525
01:26:40,992 --> 01:26:42,825
Hands in the air!

1526
01:26:42,827 --> 01:26:44,128
Now! Now!

1527
01:26:47,865 --> 01:26:49,766
Excuse me.

1528
01:26:53,037 --> 01:26:56,806
Excuse me, sirs.

1529
01:26:56,808 --> 01:27:00,009
I-I understand why my associate
is being held,

1530
01:27:00,011 --> 01:27:02,981
but what exactly am I
being charged with?

1531
01:27:05,883 --> 01:27:09,085
You seem like reasonable men.

1532
01:27:09,087 --> 01:27:10,386
Perhaps you could let me out

1533
01:27:10,388 --> 01:27:12,888
so that we could discuss
the situation further.

1534
01:27:12,890 --> 01:27:14,824
Just put the apple butter
away, boy.

1535
01:27:14,826 --> 01:27:17,827
You ain't going nowhere
no time soon.

1536
01:27:17,829 --> 01:27:20,930
You cannot hold me
without cause.

1537
01:27:20,932 --> 01:27:22,265
Well, I got cause.

1538
01:27:22,267 --> 01:27:25,036
'Cause you let the sun set
on your black ass.

1539
01:27:26,371 --> 01:27:28,971
I want to speak to my lawyer.

1540
01:27:28,973 --> 01:27:31,140
I want my call.

1541
01:27:31,142 --> 01:27:34,410
This is a flagrant violation
of my rights.

1542
01:27:34,412 --> 01:27:37,847
You know...

1543
01:27:37,849 --> 01:27:41,986
he does have, uh, rights.

1544
01:27:46,424 --> 01:27:49,859
Give the Negro
his goddamn phone call.

1545
01:27:49,861 --> 01:27:51,329
You happy?

1546
01:27:55,867 --> 01:27:57,633
You know a lawyer?

1547
01:27:57,635 --> 01:27:59,037
Call him.

1548
01:28:10,448 --> 01:28:12,181
I walk up
to the car, and I say,

1549
01:28:12,183 --> 01:28:14,050
"Sir, you know
how fast you were going?"

1550
01:28:14,052 --> 01:28:16,319
He says, "I'm sorry, Officer.
